POLOKWANE – This week will see a break from the partly cloudy and cool conditions experienced in the city over the past month. According to People’s Weather’s forecast, sunny and mild conditions are expected in Polokwane this week with temperatures set to peak in the low twenties.  Tuesday and Wednesday will be the warmest days of the week as temperatures are expected to reach a maximum of 22ºC, while minimum temperatures will peak at 10ºC. The rest of the week will peak at 20ºC, while Sunday will cool to 19ºC with partly cloudy conditions are expected. No rain has been forecast. 